# Dataset Information

## Source
**DS Salaries Dataset**  
- Kaggle: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ashifaikram/ds-salaries  
- File: `ds_salaries.csv`  
- Shape: 607 rows × 12 columns  
- Years covered: 2020, 2021, 2022

## Why data file is not included
The dataset is publicly available on Kaggle and is accessed directly  
via the Kaggle Datasets API in the notebook. Download it from the link  
above and place it as:

```
data/ds_salaries.csv
```

Or on Kaggle, add it as a dataset source — the notebook handles the path automatically.

## Columns Used

| Column | Type | Values |
|---|---|---|
| experience_level | Categorical | EN, MI, SE, EX |
| employment_type | Categorical | FT, PT, CT, FL |
| company_size | Categorical | S, M, L |
| job_title | Categorical | 50+ titles |
| remote_ratio | Numerical | 0, 50, 100 |
| work_year | Numerical | 2020, 2021, 2022 |
| salary_in_usd | Target | 2,859 – 600,000 |

## Preprocessing Applied
- Outlier removal: 5th–95th percentile on `salary_in_usd`
- Derived feature: `years_since_start = work_year - 2020`
- After cleaning: 547 rows
